<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>327</anchor>  <taxon>Theorem</taxon> <addr>axt-001V</addr>  <route>axt-001V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  The <link href="axt-001W.xml" type="local" title="Scott locale of a dcpo">Scott locale</link> of any <link href="axt-000J.xml" type="local" title="Scott domain">Scott domain</link> is algebraic.
</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>328</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001W</addr>  <route>axt-001W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date>  <title>Scott locale of a dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  The Scott locale of a dcpo <tex>D</tex> is the locale given by the frame of opens
  of the <link href="axt-001X.xml" type="local" title="Scott space of a dcpo">Scott space</link> of <tex>D</tex>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>329</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-000J</addr>  <route>axt-000J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>6</day></date> <authors><author><link href="dana-scott.xml" type="local">Dana S. Scott</link></author> </authors> <title>Scott domain</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A dcpo <tex>(D,  \sqsubseteq )</tex> is called a <em>Scott domain</em> if it is
  <ul>    <li><link href="axt-001S.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic dcpo">algebraic</link>, and</li>    <li><link href="axt-001R.xml" type="local" title="Bounded completeness">bounded complete</link>.</li>  </ul></p><p>  The definition here follows <b>Theorem 11.5</b> from <link href="dtfofp.xml" type="local" title="Domain-Theoretic Foundations of Functional Programming">Domain-Theoretic Foundations of Functional Programming</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>